definition.value: The word torticollis comes from Latin words meaning twisted neck. Spasmodic torticollis is a focal dystonia that affects the neck and sometimes the shoulders, leading to involuntary contractions of the neck muscles, abnormal movements and postures of the head and neck. The abnormal movements can have both tonic and clonic components and can results in pain and discomfort. Spasmodic torticollis is the most common focal dystonia.

https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0000474 (Thickened nuchal skin fold)  ; abnormality of head or neck ; abnormality of prenatal development or birth
preview
preview

value.value: A thickening of the skin thickness in the posterior aspect of the fetal neck. A nuchal fold (NF) measurement is obtained in a transverse section of the fetal head at the level of the cavum septum pellucidum and thalami, angled posteriorly to include the cerebellum. The measurement is taken from the outer edge of the occiput bone to the outer skin limit directly in the midline. An NF measurement greater than 5 mm at 14 to 17+6 weeks of gestation, or 6 mm at 18 to 28 weeks has been associated with a markedly increased risk for Down syndrome.

Fetal boynun arka kısmındaki deri kalınlığının kalınlaşması. Nukhal katlantı ölçümü fetal başın kavum septum pellusidum ve talamus seviyesinden serebellumu da içine alacak şekilde geriye açılanan transvers kesiminden elde edilir. Ölçüm orta hattan oksiput kemiğin dış kenarından direk deri dış sınırına alınır. 18-24 hafta arasında 6 mm veya daha fazla olan ölçüm ve 16-18 haftalar arası 5 mm veya daha fazla olan ölçüm anlamlı olarak değerlendirilir (pmid:16100637)

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: A thickening of the skin thickness in the posterior aspect of the fetal neck. A nuchal fold (NF) measurement is obtained in a transverse section of the fetal head at the level of the cavum septum pellucidum and thalami, angled posteriorly to include the cerebellum. The measurement is taken from the outer edge of the occiput bone to the outer skin limit directly in the midline. An NF measurement greater than 5 mm at 14 to 17+6 weeks of gestation, or 6 mm at 18 to 28 weeks has been associated with a markedly increased risk for Down syndrome.

value.value: Un épaississement de l'épaisseur de la peau dans la partie postérieure du cou du fœtus. La mesure du pli nucal est obtenue sur une coupe transversale de la tête du fœtus au niveau du septum pellucidum et des thalami, inclinée vers l'arrière pour inclure le cervelet. La mesure est prise du bord externe de l'os occipital à la limite externe de la peau, directement sur la ligne médiane. Une mesure de 6 mm ou plus est considérée comme significative entre 18 et 24 semaines et une mesure de 5 mm ou plus est considérée comme significative entre 16 et 18 semaines (pmid:16100637).

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: A thickening of the skin thickness in the posterior aspect of the fetal neck. A nuchal fold (NF) measurement is obtained in a transverse section of the fetal head at the level of the cavum septum pellucidum and thalami, angled posteriorly to include the cerebellum. The measurement is taken from the outer edge of the occiput bone to the outer skin limit directly in the midline. An NF measurement greater than 5 mm at 14 to 17+6 weeks of gestation, or 6 mm at 18 to 28 weeks has been associated with a markedly increased risk for Down syndrome.

value.value: Ztluštění kožní řasy šíje plodu. Měří se v transversálním řezu hlavy plodu na úrovni cavum septum pellucidum a thalamů, nakloněném tak, aby zahrnoval i mozeček. Měří se od zevního okraje okcipitální kosti po vnější okraj kůže, ve středové čáře. Tloušťka 5 mm a víc se považuje za signifikantní mezi 16. a 18. týdnem těhotenství, a tloušťka 6 mm a víc se považuje za signifikantní mezi 18. a 24. týdnem těhotenství (pmid:16100637)

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: A thickening of the skin thickness in the posterior aspect of the fetal neck. A nuchal fold (NF) measurement is obtained in a transverse section of the fetal head at the level of the cavum septum pellucidum and thalami, angled posteriorly to include the cerebellum. The measurement is taken from the outer edge of the occiput bone to the outer skin limit directly in the midline. An NF measurement greater than 5 mm at 14 to 17+6 weeks of gestation, or 6 mm at 18 to 28 weeks has been associated with a markedly increased risk for Down syndrome.

definition.value: The measurement of nuchal fold (NF) thickness during the second trimester is considered to be one of the most sensitive and specific isolated ultrasound marker for the identification of suspected cases of trisomy 21. Thick NF may also be seen in other aneuploidies as well as Turner's syndrome, Noonan's syndrome, Roberts syndrome, Zellweger syndrome and with congenital heart disease and with pathogenic CNVs. A thickened nuchal fold should be distinguished from cystic hygroma, in which the skin in this area has fluid-filled loculations. A thickened nuchal fold should not be confused with nuchal translucency, which is a specific measurement of fluid in the posterior aspect of the neck at 11 to 14 weeks gestation (see practice guidelines at http://www.sogc.org).

value.value: An inherited retinal disease subtype in which the rod photoreceptors appear to be more severely affected than the cone photoreceptors. Typical presentation is with nyctalopia (due to rod dysfunction) followed by loss of mid-peripheral field of vision, which gradually extends and leaves many patients with a small central island of vision due to the preservation of macular cones.

Un sous-type de maladie rétinienne héréditaire dans laquelle les photorécepteurs à bâtonnets semblent être plus gravement touchés que les photorécepteurs à cônes. La présentation typique est une nyctalopie (due au dysfonctionnement des bâtonnets) suivie d'une perte du champ de vision périphérique moyen, qui s'étend progressivement et laisse à de nombreux patients un petit îlot de vision centrale en raison de la préservation des cônes maculaires.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: An eye that is protruding anterior to the plane of the face to a greater extent than is typical.

definition.value: Some sources define "exophthalmos" as a protrusion of the globe greater than 18 mm and "proptosis" as a protusion equal to or less than 18 mm. Others define "exophthalmos" as protusion secondary to endocrine dysfunction and "proptosis" as any non-endocrine-mediated protusion (Source: Wikipedia). This finding should be distinguished frm underdevelopment of the supraorbital ridge or maxilla/zygoma. In proptosis, the globe is anteriorly protuberant to the overall plane of the face.
